I have been vindicated. This is the message by Moiben member of parliament Silas Tiren who now claims his political prophesy as to why he was removed as the chair of agriculture committee on January 23rd. In an interview KTN news, at that time, tiren sensationally claimed his removal was part of the wider scheme to block among other things investigation into the irregular importation of brown sugar which had a tax evasion of 2.5b. 8 months down the line, he spoke to our senior reporter Duncan Khaemba on the same, at a time when sharp divisions have emerged over a report by joint committee on trade and agriculture probing the sugar importation scam